Open Android Studio and create a new project.

Select Empty Activity and use Java as the programming language.

Add the required Firebase dependencies in the build.gradle file:

gradle
Copy code
implementation 'com.google.firebase:firebase-auth:21.4.3'
implementation 'com.google.firebase:firebase-database:20.3.3'
implementation 'com.google.android.material:material:1.9.0'
implementation 'com.google.android.gms:play-services-auth:20.6.0'
Set up Firebase for the project:

Go to the Firebase Console and create a project.
Register the app by adding the package name from your project.
Download and add the google-services.json file to your app's /app directory.
Enable Firebase Authentication for Email/Password and Google.
Set up Firebase Realtime Database and add sample data for users.
